## v2.2.0 (2026-05-10)

**Changed by:** Silent-failures ecosystem sweep — HomericIntelligence/Odysseus#280, #281 + 14 submodule PRs
**Verification:** verified-ci

### What changed
- Extended `Use when:` triggers with three new conditions related to skipping orchestrator Phase-1 when parent session has already planned
- Added section "Direct Agent fan-out as an alternative to /hephaestus:myrmidon-swarm" documenting:
  - When to skip the orchestrator skill
  - Shared brief pattern (write to ~/.tmp/<topic>-brief.md, dispatch pointer-prompts)
  - Agent feedback as brief refinement (Argus → Odysseus#281 example)
- Added one row to Failed Attempts table about orchestrator-vs-direct-Agent decision
- Added 2026-05-10 silent-failures sweep to the Session Outcome table
- Added cross-reference to new sibling skill `tooling-direct-agent-fanout-with-shared-brief`

### Why
The 2026-05-10 silent-failures sweep dispatched 14 parallel agents across all HomericIntelligence submodules. The calling session had already consulted Mnemosyne via `/advise`, planned via a Plan agent, surveyed per-repo state, and classified work into Bucket A–E — so invoking `/hephaestus:myrmidon-swarm` would have re-run all of that. Direct `Agent` dispatch with a shared brief file (~10 KB) saved ~30K tokens of parent context vs. inline-quoting instructions in 14 prompts. Two prior swarm sessions also flagged "orchestrator re-plans even when planning is complete" as friction; this amendment documents the workaround as a first-class pattern.

